The '''Stuttering Center of Western Pennsylvania''' is a partnership between the Department of Audiology and Speech-Language Pathology (Communication Disorders) at [[Children's Hospital of Pittsburgh of UPMC]] and the Department of Communication Science and Disorders in the School of Health and Rehabilitation Sciences at the [[University of Pittsburgh]].

The co-directors of the Stuttering Center are [[J. Scott Yaruss]] and Craig Coleman.

